                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": "It was Omo ti Olu-iwa bi (the child of Olu-iwa), which was shortened to Omoluwabi and later Omoluabi."
            },
            {
              "text": "In Yorubaland, an Omoluabi is someone who is of impeccable character."
            },
            {
              "text": "Simply put; Omoluabi is the word in the Yoruba language that describes an individual, male or female, young or old that possesses the following qualities: hard work, honesty, integrity, fairness, egalitarianism, respect for elders and constituted authority; and fear of God among other virtues."
